view.description:
All 311 Service Requests from 2010 to present. This information is automatically updated daily.

Click here to download data from 2011 - https://data.cityofnewyork.us/dataset/311-Service-Requests-From-2011/fpz8-jqf4

Click here to download data from 2012 - https://data.cityofnewyork.us/dataset/311-Service-Requests-From-2012/as38-8eb5

Click here to download data from 2013 - https://data.cityofnewyork.us/dataset/311-Service-Requests-From-2013/hybb-af8n

Click here to download data from 2014 - https://data.cityofnewyork.us/dataset/311-Service-Requests-From-2014/vtzg-7562

Click here to download data from 2015 - https://data.cityofnewyork.us/dataset/311-Service-Requests-From-2015/57g5-etyj

columns.name: Unique Key
columns.description: Unique identifier of a Service Request (SR) in the open data set

columns.name: Created Date
columns.description: Date SR  was created

columns.name: Closed Date
columns.description: Date SR was closed by responding agency

columns.name: Agency
columns.description: Acronym of responding City Government Agency

columns.name: Agency Name
columns.description: This is the fist level of a hierarchy identifying the topic of the incident or condition. Complaint Type may have a corresponding Descriptor (below) or may stand alone.

columns.name: Complaint Type
columns.description: Full Agency name of responding City Government Agency

columns.name: Descriptor
columns.description: This is  associated to the Complaint Type, and provides further detail on the incident or condition. Descriptor values are dependent on the Complaint Type, and are not always required in SR.

columns.name: Location Type
columns.description: Describes the type of location used in the address information

columns.name: Incident Zip
columns.description: Incident location zip code, provided by geo validation.

columns.name: Incident Address
columns.description: House number of incident address provided by submitter.

columns.name: Street Name
columns.description: Street name of incident address provided by the submitter

columns.name: Cross Street 1
columns.description: First Cross street based on the geo validated incident location

columns.name: Cross Street 2
columns.description: Second Cross Street based on the geo validated incident location

columns.name: Intersection Street 1
columns.description: First intersecting street based on geo validated incident location

columns.name: Intersection Street 2
columns.description: Second intersecting street based on geo validated incident location

columns.name: Address Type
columns.description: Type of incident location information available.

columns.name: City
columns.description: City of the incident location provided by geovalidation.

columns.name: Landmark
columns.description: If the incident location is identified as a Landmark the name of the landmark will display here

columns.name: Facility Type
columns.description: If available, this field describes the type of city facility associated to the SR

columns.name: Status
columns.description: Status of SR submitted

columns.name: Due Date
columns.description: Date when responding agency is expected to update the SR.  This is based on the Complaint Type and internal Service Level Agreements (SLAs).

columns.name: Resolution Description
columns.description: Describes the last action taken on the SR by the responding agency.  May describe next or future steps.

columns.name: Resolution Action Updated Date
columns.description: Date when responding agency last updated the SR.

columns.name: Community Board
columns.description: Provided by geovalidation.

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: Provided by the submitter and confirmed by geovalidation.

columns.name: X Coordinate (State Plane)
columns.description: Geo validated, X coordinate of the incident location.

columns.name: Y Coordinate (State Plane)
columns.description: Geo validated,  Y coordinate of the incident location.

columns.name: Park Facility Name
columns.description: If the incident location is a Parks Dept facility, the Name of the facility will appear here

columns.name: Park Borough
columns.description: The borough of incident if it is a Parks Dept facility

columns.name: School Name
columns.description: If the incident location is a Dept of Education school, the name of the school will appear in this field. If the incident is a Parks Dept facility its name will appear here.

columns.name: School Number
columns.description: If the incident location is a Dept of Education school, the Number of the school will appear in this field. This field is also used for Parks Dept Facilities.

columns.name: School Region
columns.description: If the incident location is a Dept of Education School, the school region number will be appear in this field.

columns.name: School Code
columns.description: If the incident location is a Dept of Education School, the school code number will be appear in this field.

columns.name: School Phone Number
columns.description: If the facility =  Dept for the Aging or Parks Dept, the phone number will appear here. (note - Dept of Education facilities do not display phone number)

columns.name: School Address
columns.description: Address of facility of incident location, if the facility is associated with Dept of Education, Dept for the Aging or Parks Dept

columns.name: School City
columns.description: City of facilities incident location, if the facility is associated with Dept of Education, Dept for the Aging or Parks Dept

columns.name: School State
columns.description: State of facility incident location, if the facility is associated with Dept of Education, Dept for the Aging or Parks Dept

columns.name: School Zip
columns.description: Zip of facility incident location, if the facility is associated with Dept of Education, Dept for the Aging or Parks Dept

columns.name: School Not Found
columns.description: Y' in this field indicates the facility was not found

columns.name: School or Citywide Complaint
columns.description: If the incident is about a Dept of Education facility, this field will indicate if the complaint is about a particualr school or a citywide issue.

columns.name: Vehicle Type
columns.description: If the incident is a taxi, this field describes the type of TLC vehicle.

columns.name: Taxi Company Borough
columns.description: If the incident is identified as a taxi, this field will display the borough of the taxi company.

columns.name: Taxi Pick Up Location
columns.description: If the incident is identified as a taxi, this field displays the taxi pick up location

columns.name: Bridge Highway Name
columns.description: If the incident is identified as a Bridge/Highway, the name will be displayed here.

columns.name: Bridge Highway Direction
columns.description: If the incident is identified as a Bridge/Highway, the direction where the issue took place would be displayed here.

columns.name: Road Ramp
columns.description: If the incident location was Bridge/Highway this column differentiates if the issue was on the Road or the Ramp.

columns.name: Bridge Highway Segment
columns.description: Additional information on the section of the Bridge/Highway were the incident took place.

columns.name: Garage Lot Name
columns.description: Related to DOT Parking Meter SR, this field shows what garage lot the meter is located in

columns.name: Ferry Direction
columns.description: Used when the incident location is within a Ferry, this field indicates the direction of ferry

columns.name: Ferry Terminal Name
columns.description: Used when the incident location is Ferry, this field indicates the ferry terminal where the incident took place.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Geo based Lat of the incident location

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Geo based Long of the incident location

columns.name: Location
columns.description: Combination of the geo based lat & long of the incident location
